{ The Italian is a trendy opening even on the very top levels and it allows us to play variations that feature both tactical skirmishes and important positional ideas. }
3... Be7 { This move neglects the center, the same way  3...h6  does. } 4. d4
exd4 5. Nxd4 Nf6 6. Nc3 O-O 7. O-O d6 8. Bf4
{ White is better due to our space advantage and greater piece mobility. Our plans include Nxc6 followed by e5, as well as the natural development of the heavy pieces with Qd2, Rfe1, and Rad1. }
