9... Nbd7
{ Black brings another piece in, aiming to attack e4 yet again. This line perfectly demonstrates how individual moves are part of a far larger picture. }
10. Re1
{ White prophylactically defends the e4-pawn @@StartBracket@@meaning - before it even gets attacked by Nc5@@EndBracket@@, so that we have ample choices when the knight lands on c5. }
10... Nc5 11. Nb3 { This lovely move trades off Black's best piece. } 11...
Nxb3 12. axb3
{ White's position is clearly preferable due to our better piece mobility and space advantage in the center. }
