[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "5) Damiano Defense, Elephant Gambit and Latvian Gambit"]
[Black "Elephant Gambit #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 d5
{ This is the so-called Elephant Gambit, but do not be fooled! Unlike its namesake, the opening is neither sturdy nor long-lived.  Such early impulsive moves are usually soundly punished and this is no exception! }
3. exd5
{ This is the correct capture. White is tempting Black to bring their queen out too early. }
3... Qxd5 4. Nc3 Qa5 5. Bc4
{ As is often the case in e4-e5 openings, White takes aim at the weak f7-pawn. }
5... Nc6 6. O-O Bg4 { This is a classical motif that loses on the spot. } 7.
Bxf7+ Kxf7 8. Ng5+
{ Proving the age-old chess wisdom that one should be careful when pinning with an unguarded piece! }
8... Ke8 9. Qxg4
{ White is winning. White’s plan is simply to complete development by d2-d3, Bd2, Rfe1, and begin an assault against the black king that has lost its castling rights. }
*

