2... Nc6
{ This is the most commonly played move at the club level, which often leads to early opening disasters. }
3. d4 cxd4 4. cxd4 d5 5. exd5 Qxd5 6. Nf3 Bg4
{ This is one of the most popular lines according to the lichess database, but it is actually a move that leads to very unpleasant positions for Black. }
7. Nc3
{ Not only is this move the engine's first choice but it is also the most principled and most aggressive! }
7... Bxf3 { Completely forced, other moves are hardly playable. } 8. gxf3 Qxd4
{ The outline of the upcoming positions is already clear: White will have superior development and the bishop pair to boot. In contrast, Black will have to begin the early middlegame with a completely untouched kingside! }
