{ And White has emerged from the complications with a clear edge. The a8-knight is safely out, whereas the a1 one is still to be rescued. Our main follow-up idea is Kc1, rounding up the knight. Although Black is not entirely out of resources, White has all the pluses: two bishops, great piece coordination, and the terribly misplaced a1-knight to play against. }
