[White "6.2) Alapin Sicilian - Model Games"]
[Black "D. Pavasovic - A. Kopylov, Khanty-Mansiysk 2010"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. c3 d5 4. exd5 Qxd5 5. d4 Nf6 6. Be3 cxd4 7. cxd4 Nc6 8.
Nc3 Qd6 9. a3 Be7 10. Bd3 O-O 11. O-O b6 12. Qe2 Bb7 13. Rad1 Rac8 14. Bb1 Rfd8
15. Rfe1 Qc7 16. Bg5
{ After completing development, White is signaling the upcoming attack. The move puts pressure on f6 and therefore, indirectly on h7 and the d5-square too. }
16... Nd5 17. Qe4
{ Another typical motif. Black is now forced to weaken the kingside. } 17... g6
18. Qh4 h5
{ This is just too much. Black collapses under the pressure.   18...Nxc3  19.bxc3  Re8  would have been more tenacious. }
19. Bxg6 fxg6 20. Rxe6 Kf7 21. Rde1 Bf8 22. Qe4
{ 22.Bh6!!  would have been a fantastic knockout, although the text is also totally winning:  22...Bxh6  23.Nxd5  Rxd5  24.Qf6+  Kg8  25.Re8+  Rxe8  26.Rxe8+  Kh7  27.Rh8  . }
22... Nce7 23. Rxe7+ Nxe7 24. Qe6+ Kg7 25. Bf6+ Kh6 26. Qe3+ g5
{ White also wins afer  26...Kh7  27.Ng5+  Kh6  28.Ne6+  . } 27. Qxg5+ Kh7 28.
Rxe7+
{ This wins the house, but even deadlier would have been:  28.Nh4  28...Rd6  29.Rxe7+  Qxe7  30.Qg6  . }
