{ This novelty is actually a key component of the line. In order the understand this move we need to appreciate Black's defensive idea against  11.Nxf3  which leads to a slightly worse endgame after  11...Qxb4  12.Rb1  Qa4!  @@StartBracket@@the key idea of the defense@@EndBracket@@  13.Qxa4  Bxa4  14.Rxb7  Ne7  and White's counterplay fizzles out. }
11... Bxb4 12. Rb1 Qa5 13. Qg4 { Black is in trouble now. } 13... Bf8 14. Rxb7
