[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "10) Scandinavian "]
[Black "Scandinavian: 2...Qxd5 3.Nc3 Qd8 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 d5
{ This move introduces the Scandinavian Defense. In the main line, Black moves their queen out early, which is unprincipled. On that account, we immediately set about exploiting it! }
2. exd5 Qxd5 3. Nc3 { We immediately attack the queen. } 3... Qd8
{ This is a very passive move that allows us to freely develop and occupy the center. }
4. d4
{ Whenever the opportunity arises to conquer the center, we should take it! }
4... Nf6 5. Nf3 Nc6
{ This move is almost always bad in the Scandi as White usually gets to play d4-d5 at one point. }
6. Bb5 Bd7 7. O-O { White's lead in development continues to grow. } 7... e6 8.
d5
{ Again, the principled move: The opponent's king is stuck in the middle, so we should open files towards it. }
8... exd5 9. Nxd5 Nxd5 10. Qxd5 Be7 11. Rd1
{ This move prevents Black from castling because of the hanging bishop on d7.  11.Re1  , in contrast, would not do the same. }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
