[Result "*"]

1. e4 d5
{ This move introduces the Scandinavian Defense. In the main line, Black moves their queen out early, which is unprincipled. On that account, we immediately set about exploiting it! }
2. exd5 Qxd5 3. Nc3 { We immediately attack the queen. } 3... Qd8
{ This is a very passive move that allows us to freely develop and occupy the center. }
4. d4
{ Whenever the opportunity arises to conquer the center, we should take it! }
4... Nf6 5. Nf3 Bg4 6. h3
{ While the pin poses no threat, chasing the bishop around allows us extra tempi to develop and gain momentum on the kingside. In the meantime, Black loses valuable time that they could have spent developing the rest of their army. }
6... Bxf3 7. Qxf3 c6 8. g4
{ We are trying to tempt Black to capture on d4, thus further delaying their development. }
8... Qxd4 9. Be3 Qd8
{ Black has played four queen moves out of nine, which more than justifies the material we just sacrificed. }
10. g5 Nd5 11. O-O-O e6 12. Nxd5
{ After this trade, Black has to play with extreme accuracy just to stay in the game! }
12... exd5 13. Re1
{ This surprising move essentially wins the game on the spot as Black has no adequate answer to the threatening discovered checks/attacks. }
