1. e4 d5
{ This move introduces the Scandinavian Defense. In the main line, Black moves their queen out early, which is unprincipled. On that account, we immediately set about exploiting it! }
2. exd5 Qxd5 3. Nc3 { We immediately attack the queen. } 3... Qd6 4. d4 Nf6 5.
Nf3 a6 6. g3
{ White is aiming to fianchetto their bishop, whilst also supporting the development of the other bishop to f4. }
6... b5 7. Bg2 Bb7 8. O-O
{ This move has a dual purpose: Other than securing the king, it also defends the g2-bishop, allowing the f3-knight to actively participate in the battle. }
8... e6 9. Bf4 Qb6 10. a4
{ This is the key move, which allows us to take advantage of our better-developed army. }
10... Bd6 11. Be3
{ Once again, making the queen feel ill at ease. White is clearly on top with our superior development.  If  11...b4  then  12.a5!  Qa7  13.Na4  . }
