1. e4 d5
{ This move introduces the Scandinavian Defense. In the main line, Black moves their queen out early, which is unprincipled. On that account, we immediately set about exploiting it! }
2. exd5 Qxd5 3. Nc3 { We immediately attack the queen. } 3... Qa5 4. d4 Nf6 5.
Nf3 Bg4 6. h3 { Our usual response to the premature pinning of the knight. }
6... Bxf3 7. Qxf3 c6 8. Bd2
{ As usual in these scenarios, we prefer to castle queenside in order to bring the a1-rook into the battle right away. }
8... e6 9. O-O-O Nbd7 10. Bd3 { Developing our last minor piece. } 10... Qb6
11. Be3 { Threatening d5 with a discovered attack on the queen. } 11... Nd5 12.
Nxd5 cxd5 13. g4
{ White has a very comfortable attacking position with nothing to worry about. White’s main plan is to pawn storm on the kingside with g4-g5, h4-h5, and eventually g5-g6! }
