[Black "St. George Defense: 1...a6 #2"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 a6
{ This is the St. George Defense, a 'close relative' of the Owen's Defense both in structure and strategy. }
2. d4 b5 3. Nf3
{ As one of my favorite 'rules of thumb' says: 'Weird stuff gets beaten by regular stuff', and in this spirit, White plays simple, natural developing moves. }
3... Bb7 4. Bd3 e6 5. O-O
{ White has full control of the center and is safely castled. One can't possibly ask for more in an opening! }
5... c5 6. c3 { We insist on retaining our central pawn formation. } 6... Nf6
7. e5 Nd5 8. dxc5
{ Although this move releases the tension and gives up the center, its benefits are also numerous: White will have easy access to the center with Nbd2-e4, and also be able to challenge the b5-pawn with a4. }
8... Bxc5 9. Nbd2 Nc6 10. a4
{ Black is now struggling to find a good response. } 10... Qc7
{ Black's best move. } 11. axb5 axb5 12. Rxa8+ Bxa8 13. Re1
{ White stands better as Black is struggling to keep the b5-pawn alive. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "12) Miscellaneous"]
[Black "Nimzowitsch Defense: 1...Nc6 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 Nc6
{ This move introduces the Nimzowitsch Defense. A common response at the club level here is  2.Nf3  , hoping to steer the game back towards e4-e5 openings. This, however, is not in line with our principles: When e4 and d4 is allowed, we shall take the center! }
2. d4 e5
{ Yet another invitation to an e4 opening, this time  3.Nf3  would lead to the Scotch. We, however, aim to punish this setup in a more aggressive way. }
3. dxe5 Nxe5 4. Nf3 Nxf3+ 5. gxf3
{ This odd-looking recapture is one of our main plans. White intends to castle queenside and use the semi-open g-file as an avenue of attack.   Black's main problem is that it is hard to see how they can contest White in the center as the d7-d5 break seems extremely difficult to achieve! }
5... Nf6 6. Nc3 d6
{ This allows White to achieve a very comfortable attacking setup. } 7. Be3 g6
8. Qd2 Bg7 9. O-O-O O-O 10. Bh6
{ White's attack is in full swing, whereas Black has not even completed development yet. }
*

